Major News Items in Leading Nigerian Newspapers
LAGOS , November 19 ( Xinhua ) -- The following are major news items in leading Nigerian newspapers Thursday :
New Nigerian :
-- The Nigerian government is making arrangements to accelerate projects execution in the oil producing states , Nigerian Head of State General Abdulsalam Abubakar said Wednesday .
-- British Assistant Chief of Defense Staff Major General Christopher Drewry arrived in capital Abuja Wednesday for a three-day visit to Nigeria .
The Guardian :
-- Procedural details for the nascent debate on the 1995 draft constitution were reeled out Wednesday by the Nigerian Constitutional Debate Coordinating Committee .
The Post Express :
-- Nigerian Head of State Abdulsalam Abubakar Wednesday pledged that all draconian decrees in the nation 's statute books would be repealed " very soon " during his on-going nationwide tour of states .
This Day :
-- The Nigerian government has unfolded plans to calm the prevailing tension in Niger River Delta area which has witnessed several clashes between oil producing companies and local communities demanding for modern infrastructure .
Nigerian Tribune :
-- A senior official of the International Monetary Fund ( IMF ) disclosed Wednesday that IMF had commenced discussion with top Nigerian officials on how best to assist the country in reducing its external debts .
